Notre Dame Cycling Classic
description: Notre Dame Cycling Classic Presented by Gurley Leep and the Bilal and Shamaila Ansari Foundation on Sunday, April 14, 2013. MWCCC Race
course:
The 4-corner, 1.1km criterium course is flat and fast. It is located in beautiful downtown South Bend, IN, finishing 350m from the final corner in front of the College Football Hall of Fame. There are two coffee 
shops on the course that open at 8am on Sundays to provide ample caffeine for early morning racers and 
spectators. There are also local breakfast and chain lunch establishments on the course if racers wish to eat 
before or after races. Parking downtown is available in a number of public lots, along streets, and in a public 
parking garage one block north of the race course on IN 933.
registration: Online registration is $15 per entry. There is a $5 late fee per entry for on-site entries. Registration opens 1 hour and closes 15 minutes prior to the start of each race.
notes:
Races will be held rain or shine. All times are EASTERN. Must hold and Annual USAC Road license in order to participate in Non-Collegiate road races
The following are host hotels within a 10-minute drive from the course. They have rooms available at a discounted rate until at least March 15. Contact for details. 
Quality Inn: 215 Dixie Way S, South Bend, IN 46637, phone: 574-277-3211
Waterford Estates Lodge: 52890 SR 933 N, South Bend, IN 46637, phone: 574-273-6184
directions: Address: 111 S. Saint Joseph Street, South Bend, IN, 46601

title: Kenda DINO Mountain Bike Series- Warsaw
Winona Lake Criterium & Winona Road Rac
Get Dirty Mtb Race
description:
A unique race day with two events for one low price. The day kicks off with a 5 mile time trial followed by a cross country race of 5 to 15 miles.

The time trial will set the start grid for the cross country race. You can do either event or both. It\'s just one low price for both events.

We will have an award for the fastest time trial lap, the fastest cross country race, and a combined overall winner.
course: The 5 mile loop at Angel Mounds will be used for both events. It\'s mostly flat, very fast route with some quick turns and slight elevation changes.
registration: There is jsut one price for both events. You can register for just the time trial, just the cross country race, or both events.
notes: For new racers or riders that aren\'t comforatable with racing side by side yet, we encourage you to enter the time trial, it\'s just you and the clock.
directions:
The race is being held at Angel Mounds State Historical Site-

8215 Pollack Ave
Evansville, IN, 47715

Indy Criterium Cycling Race & Festival
description:
The 4th annual Indy Criterium is sure to challenge the racers and thrill the spectators.  Situated in the heart of Downtown Indianapolis, the Indy Crit offers cyclists a unique opportunity to race the city streets that they would rarely ride otherwise.

Last year's event drew over 520 racers!!  Be a part of the fun and excitement of Indiana's largest criterium race!

Race Highlights
  •  Over $8,000 in Cash & Prizes, including $1,300 in cash primes!
  •  $20 Gift Certificate for The Bike Line provided to all registered racers
  •  Podium ceremony on stage for all categories
  •  Call-ups for first 20 pre-registered in each category
  •  Unique figure-8 course in the heart of the city
  •  Neutral Wheel Support 
  •  Pre-Registration Contest: Top prize is a set of Zipp 303 Firecrest Wheels ($2,700 value)
  •  Free swag at Registration table

Festival Highlights
  •  Food Trucks, Beer Garden, Vendors, Music
  •  Morning Indy Crit Kick-Off Ride
  •  Family "EXPLORE INDY" Rides 
  •  Kids Races & Activities 
  •  Tandem & Strider Races (open to public)
  •  Free bike parking at Pedal & Park!

The Indy Criterium is an official non-profit 501(c)3 event.  All event proceeds benefit Freewheelin' Community Bikes.
course:
•  0.95 mile closed course
  •  Wide lanes / flat course
  •  Unique figure-8 race course 
  •  Race on the bricks of Monument Circle
notes:
Free parking available to racers at:
"CENTRAL PARK” PARKING GARAGE
301 N. ILLINOIS ST.
INDIANAPOLIS, IN 46204

Held under USA Cycling permit.  All USA Cycling rules apply.  Free-lap rule is in effect.  Lapped riders may be pulled at the officials discretion.  You must present a valid 2013 USA Cycling license at registration to enter any race.  Only Category 5 men and Category 4 women may purchase a one-day license for $10 at registration.  Promoter reserves the right to shorten, modify, cancel or combine any race or prize list in the event of insufficient entries or bad weather.  All winners must be present to receive prizes/awards.  Day of race registration opens at 8:30am and closes 30 minutes before the start of each race.  $20 fee for each additional race.  Pre-registration closes at 1159pm EST on 7/10/13. $10 late fee applies for race day registration. Helmets required.  No refunds.

title: INMTB Town Run XC Night Race
Terre Haute Criterium
description: Crossroads Events LLC would like to welcome you to the 2013 Terre Haute Criterium! The criterium takes place within Fairbanks Park on the banks of the beautiful Wabash River. The event will be on a fast closed course with a packed venue of spectators to cheer you on! So bring your A game and come race with us!
course: The course takes place within Fairbanks park on a fast 1/2 mile closed course with 3 turns. There is a quick short downhill between turns 1 and 2 with the majority of the course consisting of a slight gradual uphill. Most of the venue provides very wide roads for easy maneuverability.
notes: Please park in the grass near the start/finish line within Fairbanks Park next to 1st street. Do not park in the YMCA parking lots you will be asked to move. Please note that registration will be $40.00 on the day of the event. Registration will be at the large wooden shelter next to the parking area.
directions: Fairbanks Park Address: Dresser Drive Terre Haute, IN 47807

Bloomingcross
description: This event is part of the 2013 Ohio Valley Cyclocross Series and is the first race in the series.
course: A challenging, fast course that favors technique and speed.
registration:
For series schedule of events and complete rules & info, please visit www.OVCX.COM.:  For racers that miss pre-registration, walk-up registration will be available at the race for an additional $10.  The registration table opens up 2 hours before the start of the first race.  Registration closes for an event 45 minutes before its start. Start Line Staging: All categories scheduled to start at the same time will go off in one wave, with individual categories intermixed.  First to be staged on the line are those that pre-register at least 2 weeks out from the close of pre-reg, and they will be staged by their Crossresults.com ranking (if applicable).  Next staged will be everyone that pre-registers from 2 weeks out til the close of pre-registration – and they also will be staged by their Crossresults.com ranking (if applicable).  Those that register on raceday will line up at the back.  This system will work for all combined categories going off the starting line at the same time.  Each category will get scored separately as well, and get a podium celebration each day as well as OVCX series points for their category.

Chip Timing:  Each rider is provided a free custom OVCX timing chip for the top of their helmet at their first OVCX race they attend.  It can and should be used the entirety of the OVCX Series.  If they are lost, chip must be replaced at a cost of $10.  Event results will contain finish times, as well as splits for each lap.
